 alleys and intercept one of the two Loom keys without killing, taking the bite from the plan before it can close its jaws.\",\n        \"Slip or storm your way into the private parley between Mara Vell-Seren and Verrin Nasse and obtain the ledger pact that binds loans to engineered catastrophe, keeping its ink intact as lawful leverage.\",\n        \"Reach the service gallery where the bypass wheel hums like a throat and hold it against the tide’s pull until Rusk Bonebinder’s sabotage jam cures hard in the teeth of the gears.\",\n        \"Stand before Verrin Nasse in the breath of the Loom, and by truth, threat, or skillful plea, persuade or force him to stand down from the demonstration and surrender his remaining key and chorus.\",\n        \"Carry the seized key and the ledger pact to the Council guard at the Vertebrae and demand an immediate injunction under fossil chandeliers before the Compact or Keyholders can recast the tale.\"\n      ],\n      \"dialogue\": [\n        {\n          \"speaker\": \"Captain Ysger Thorn\",\n          \"lines\": \"When I was a young sergeant, a flood ate a ward because a man wanted to win an argument, and I learned that some victories are just funerals that forgot the prayers. He won it, and I can still hear the quiet after the water went home and found nothing left to drown. The Tide Looms are a beast on a chain, and fools love to test the length of it with other people’s lungs. I won’t watch another man gamble with the looms because he fancies himself a storm, not while my oath still tastes of salt. Take the wind out of his lungs, Kael, and take the shine off every coin they tried to stack on this disaster, because if the market runs dry by their hand, the city will drink their lies like rain.\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"speaker\": \"Kael Rimestrand\",\n          \"lines\": \"I have seen a ward go quiet and I have listened to whalesong fade under iron weather, and I won’t let a demonstration write a eulogy. I’ll tak